It is also the first time where a study of the formal properties of the negotiation theories of the agents as well as of an argumentative  negotiation dialogue is presented.
This work is a first attempt to formally define the role of  argumentation in the negotiation process.
More precisely , for the first time , it formally establishes the link that exists between the status of the arguments and the offers they support , it defines the notion of concession and shows how it influences the evolution of the negotiation , it determines how the theories of agents evolve during 